article.headline: Delaware 54, Northeastern 52
article.story: NEWARK, Del. -- Jamelle Hagins' dunk with 21 seconds left lifted Delaware over Northeastern 54-52 on Wednesday night. The Blue Hens (9-8, 4-3 Colonial Athletic Association) trailed 52-45 with 3:46 to play before going on a 9-0 run the rest of the way. A three-point play by Kelvin McNeil sparked the game-winning spurt. After Hagins' dunk, the Huskies (4-14, 0-7) missed two jump shots, including one in the lane with 1 second left. Delaware made just 7 of 27 from the field in the first half and trailed 28-22 at halftime. However, the Blue Hens shot 50 percent (12 of 24) and turned it over just once in the second half. Delaware finished with a season-low three turnovers in snapping an 11-game losing streak against Northeastern. Hagins, who leads the conference in blocked shots (4.6 per game), had a career-high eight against the Huskies. Joel Smith led Northeastern with 18 points.
